TextArea.Text: Developing applications for Virtual Reality systems is difficult because of the hardware required, sophistication of Virtual Reality software, and the technical expertise required to use them. The Kabala Engine has been designed to bridge the divide between non-technical users and virtual reality application development. The Kabala Engine is an open source application that allows users to build dynamic relationships with multimedia content and interactive components into a user-created application. Once the relationships have been designed, the engine can then run the user-created application in a virtual reality system that has vrjuggler configuration. I intend to test the effectiveness of the Kabala Engine to increase the accessibility of creating applications for virtual reality systems.

The view into the 3D environment can be navigated by moving, rotating, and zooming the camera.
Move: Press and hold ALT, and then right-click and pull. This will move the camera from side-to-side.
Rotate: Press and hold ALT, and then left-click and pull. This will rotate the camera.
Zoom: Spin the mouse-wheel forward and backwards to zoom the scene in and out.
Select Scene objects: Left-click on the 3D geometry of a scene object. This will select the scene-object. You will notice that the triangle mesh of the geometry will be drawn in pink.
Focus Camera: To focus the camera on a scene object, first select the scene object and press the focus tool. The focus tool looks like an eye.

Scene objects are the primary 3D objects in a scene.
Create a new scene object: Click on the + button next to the Scene Objects label on the left panel. This will open a file browser where you can select the 3D geometry file you would like to use for this new scene object.

The Background of a scene is the color that is drawn where there is no 3D geometry. You can change the color of the background of a scene by selecting the background in the left panel. After that the right panel will show the settings that can be changed for the background.
